HEADWORD: Biodynamics
<hw>Bi`o*dy*nam"ics</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>bi`os</grk> life + E. <ets>dynamics</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The doctrine of vital forces or energy.</def>
<mark>[archaic]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The branch of biology which treats of the active
vital phenomena of organisms; -- opposed to
<contr>biostatics</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>bioelectricity</ent>⟦br⟧
